criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of COPD in stage II or III according to classification of the Global
             Initiative for Chronic Obstructive Lung Disease (GOLD);

          -  Signing the consent form;

          -  Stability of clinical pathology, with no signs of exacerbation in the 30 (thirty) days
             prior to the inclusion in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals would use artificial airway;

          -  Hemodynamic instability;

          -  Body mass index (BMI) above the values considered as obese (> 30Kg/m2).
